==English==
===Etymology===
The word "epistemology" literally means "to base all knowledge on understanding within reason". It comes from the Greek words [[επιστήμη]] ''[[(episteme)]]'' meaning "knowledge, understanding" and [[λόγος]] (''[[logos]]'') meaning "reason, grounds". From [[επι-]] "upon" and [[εστάναι]] "to place".


